cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with load balancing in data centers hosting cloud computation, which falls under the scope of distributed and cluster computing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of on-demand cloud services, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel approach for cost savings in load balancing, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses Service Level Agreements (SLAs) to differentiate among workloads, which can be seen as a computational engineering problem. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper presents online algorithms for workload assignment and migration, which can be seen as a software engineering problem.
